# VLAN & Subnet Plan

## Base Network
- Given Network: 192.168.1.0/24  
- Requirement: Divided into 4 equal subnets for VLANs  
- Subnet Mask Calculation:  
  - /24 â†’ 255.255.255.0 (256 addresses)  
  - Needed 4 subnets â†’ borrow 2 bits â†’ /26 mask = 255.255.255.192  
  - Each /26 = 64 addresses (62 usable hosts + 1 network + 1 broadcast)  


## Subnet Allocation

### VLAN 10 â€“ Sales (SW1)
- Subnet: 192.168.1.0/26  
- Subnet Mask: 255.255.255.192 (/26)  
- Network Address: 192.168.1.0  
- First Usable Host: 192.168.1.1  
- Last Usable Host: 192.168.1.62  
- Broadcast:** 192.168.1.63  
- Default Gateway (R1 Subinterface): 192.168.1.1  


### VLAN 20 â€“ Engineering (SW1)
- Subnet: 192.168.1.64/26  
- Subnet Mask: 255.255.255.192 (/26)  
- Network Address: 192.168.1.64  
- First Usable Host: 192.168.1.65  
- Last Usable Host: 192.168.1.126  
- Broadcast: 192.168.1.127  
- Default Gateway (R1 Subinterface): 192.168.1.65  


### VLAN 30 â€“ HR (SW2)
- Subnet: 192.168.1.128/26  
- Subnet Mask: 255.255.255.192 (/26)  
- Network Address: 192.168.1.128  
- First Usable Host: 192.168.1.129  
- Last Usable Host: 192.168.1.190  
- Broadcast: 192.168.1.191  
- Default Gateway (R1 Subinterface): 192.168.1.129  


### VLAN 40 â€“ Service (SW2)
- Subnet: 192.168.1.192/26  
- Subnet Mask: 255.255.255.192 (/26)  
- Network Address: 192.168.1.192  
- First Usable Host: 192.168.1.193  
- Last Usable Host: 192.168.1.254  
- Broadcast: 192.168.1.255  
- Default Gateway (R1 Subinterface): 192.168.1.193  

